The Telegraph - Calcutta
 Superstars for Mumbai Marathon
Mumbai: The worlds top 10 men and women long-distance runners will compete in the Mumbai Marathon to be held on February 15. The high-profile field in the countrys first-ever international marathon includes Commonwealth Games champion Francis Robert Naali of Tanzania and five-time womens world champion Ham Bong Sil of Korea. Indian Olympic Association (IOA) president Suresh Kalmadi said this will be the biggest prize-money marathon in Asia. The $ 200,000 meet will also bring together former champions like South African Zola Budd, long jump record-holder Mike Powell, 400m world record-holder Michael Johnson and 1996 Olympic marathon champion Josiah Thugwane in action. Other runners to vie for glory include Zacharia Mpolokeng and Hendrik Ramaala (both South Africa), Ashelsir Demissie and Semeretu Alemayehu (both Ethiopia), Patrick Chumba, Henry Tarus and Willie Cheryiot (all from Kenya) and Leonid Shvetsov of Russia. (PTI)  Copyright 
